    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - INSTALL - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>There are two (2) sizes of bolts. The 1-1/2" ; bolts are used with the lifting eyes.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Apply Eaton/Fuller gasket sealant #71233 or Loctite Spray-A-Gasket to the shifter housing before
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the shift bars in the neutral position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the synchronizers in the neutral position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026j1">Figure 191</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026j1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026j1" filename="../figg13/g13026j1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 191. Place Synchronizers in Neutral Position</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new shifter housing gasket on the shifter housing mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026j2">Figure 192</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026j2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026j2" filename="../figg13/g13026j2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 192. Position New Shifter Housing Gasket on Shifter Housing Mounting Surface and Install
                    Shifter Housing
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">As you install the shifter housing, make sure the yokes fit into the corresponding
                synchronizers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026j2">Figure 192</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite 242 or equivalent to the retaining bolts, if not precoated.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the center rear retaining bolt first and the center front retaining bolt second.
                Tighten to 35 to 40 ft-lbs. (47 to 54 N&#8226; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026j3">Figure 193</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026j3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026j3" filename="../figg13/g13026j3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 193. Install Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the remaining bolts; tighten to 35 to 40 ft-lbs. (47 to 54 N&#8226; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026j4">Figure 194</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026j4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026j4" filename="../figg13/g13026j4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 194. Install Remaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
